WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.617 --> 00:00:08.327
When they analyzed the stock market up to 9.11. -

2
00:00:08.357 --> 00:00:11.537
- the CIA discovered a massive shortage of airline stocks.

3
00:00:11.737 --> 00:00:15.687
When the stock hit the bottom on 9.11.
somebody made a fortune.

4
00:00:15.887 --> 00:00:19.247
The same thing happened this morning
with Skyfleet stock. or was supposed to.

5
00:00:19.447 --> 00:00:23.397
With their prototype destroyed. the company
would have been a bancrupcy.

6
00:00:23.597 --> 00:00:28.147
Instead. somebody lost over 100 million dollars
betting the wrong way.

7
00:00:28.347 --> 00:00:30.807
You think this man was Le Chiffre?

8
00:00:30.837 --> 00:00:35.067
Which would explain how he could set up a
high stakes poker game at Casino Royale in Montenegro.

9
00:00:35.267 --> 00:00:39.227
10 players. $10 million buy in. $5 millioner re-buy

10
00:00:39.417 --> 00:00:41.997
Winner takes all. potentially $150 millions.

11
00:00:42.187 --> 00:00:46.587
Good. then we know where he'll be. Do you want
a clean kill or do you want to send a message?

12
00:00:46.787 --> 00:00:51.137
We want him alive.
Le Chiffre doesn't have a $100 million to loose.

13
00:00:51.337 --> 00:00:54.937
He played the stock market with his client's funds?

14
00:00:54.967 --> 00:00:57.317
They won't be too happy when they find out it's gone.

15
00:00:57.517 --> 00:01:01.367
We can't let him win this game. If he looses.
he has nowhere to run.

16
00:01:01.377 --> 00:01:04.337
We'll give him sanfry in return for everything he knows.

17
00:01:04.537 --> 00:01:08.677
I'm putting you in the game.
Replacing someone playing for a syndicate.

18
00:01:08.687 --> 00:01:11.657
According to Villiers. you are the best player in the Service.

19
00:01:12.647 --> 00:01:14.817
Thust me. I wish it wasn't the case.

20
00:01:18.777 --> 00:01:22.237
I would ask you if you could remain emotionally detached.

21
00:01:23.327 --> 00:01:28.077
- But I know that's not your problem. is it Boond? - No.

22
00:01:30.937 --> 00:01:34.987
Don't worry about keeping in touch. We know where you are.

23
00:01:34.997 --> 00:01:39.047
You can stop pretending.
You knew I wouldn't let it stop. didn't you?

24
00:01:40.137 --> 00:01:42.117
When I knew you were you.

25
00:02:08.267 --> 00:02:10.247
I am the money.

26
00:02:12.077 --> 00:02:14.057
Every penny of it.

27
00:02:15.637 --> 00:02:18.607
The treasury has agreed to stake you in the game.

28
00:02:18.797 --> 00:02:22.857
Vesper. I hope your parent had it for that.

29
00:02:23.647 --> 00:02:25.567
Thank you.

30
00:02:25.577 --> 00:02:30.367
You must be well connected. I've never seen
so much be done so quickly.

31
00:02:30.407 --> 00:02:32.387
Or so stylishly.

32
00:02:33.727 --> 00:02:37.687
- May I ask you where it is? -
$10 millions was wired to your account in Montenegro.

33
00:02:37.887 --> 00:02:41.997
With contuingency for 5 more.
if I deem it a good looking investment.

34
00:02:42.337 --> 00:02:45.387
I suppose you've given some thought
to the notion that if you loose. -

35
00:02:45.397 --> 00:02:49.677
- our government would have directly financed terrorism.

36
00:02:59.637 --> 00:03:02.607
So you're telling me it's a matter of probability?

37
00:03:02.807 --> 00:03:04.777
I was worried it was some chance involved.

38
00:03:04.977 --> 00:03:07.057
You'll never see the player with the best hand win.

39
00:03:07.747 --> 00:03:09.727
So that'll be what you call bluffing.

40
00:03:12.397 --> 00:03:14.377
You've heard the term?

41
00:03:14.467 --> 00:03:18.427
Then you'll know that in poker you never
play your hand. but the man's across from you.

42
00:03:18.627 --> 00:03:21.237
- And you are good at reading people? - Yes. I am.

43
00:03:21.267 --> 00:03:25.217
Which is why I've noticed an undertone
of sarcasm in your voice.

44
00:03:25.547 --> 00:03:27.917
-

45
00:03:29.307 --> 00:03:33.057
- You don't think this is a very good plan. do you? -
So there is a plan?

46
00:03:33.067 --> 00:03:38.197
I got the impression we were risking millions of dollars and hundreds of lives in a game of luck.

47
00:03:38.207 --> 00:03:41.767
- What else can you advice. mr. Bond? - About you. miss Lynd?

48
00:03:42.657 --> 00:03:44.527
Well. your beauty is a problem.

49
00:03:44.537 --> 00:03:47.067
You worry you're not being taken seriously.

50
00:03:47.097 --> 00:03:49.867
Which is what you can say of any effective
woman with a heart and brain.

51
00:03:49.877 --> 00:03:53.427
True. but this one overcompensates by
wearing slugging masculine clothing -

52
00:03:53.437 --> 00:03:57.977
- and being more aggresive than her female collegues.

53
00:03:58.177 --> 00:04:03.917
And ironically enough. and makes it less likely
for her to be accepted and promoted by her male superiors. -

54
00:04:04.107 --> 00:04:07.067
- and mistake it a curtesy for arrogance.

55
00:04:07.077 --> 00:04:10.537
Now I'd normally go with "only child". but -

56
00:04:14.887 --> 00:04:16.967
- I would go for "Orphan".

57
00:04:19.837 --> 00:04:21.817
All right.

58
00:04:22.107 --> 00:04:25.757
By the cut of your suit you went to Oxford. -

59
00:04:25.767 --> 00:04:29.817
- naturally thinking that human beings are dressed
like that. but you worried it was demanded.

60
00:04:30.017 --> 00:04:33.977
My guess is that you didn't come from money.
and your school friends never let you forget it.

61
00:04:34.177 --> 00:04:37.537
Which means that you were at that school
by the grace of someone else's charity.

62
00:04:37.737 --> 00:04:43.367
And since you first thought of me being as an orphan.
I would say that you are.

63
00:04:47.717 --> 00:04:51.477
And you are? I like this poker thing.

64
00:04:51.967 --> 00:04:53.837
And that makes perfect sense. -

65
00:04:53.847 --> 00:05:00.677
- since MI6 looks for an adjusted young man who gives little
thought to sacrificing others in order to protect queen and country.

66
00:05:01.267 --> 00:05:06.207
You know. former SAS types with
easy smiles and expensive watches.

67
00:05:06.607 --> 00:05:08.777
- Rolex? - Omega.

68
00:05:08.787 --> 00:05:10.757
Beautiful.

69
00:05:11.157 --> 00:05:16.097
Now. after having first met you. I wouldn't go
as far as calling you a cold hearted bastard.

70
00:05:16.297 --> 00:05:19.067
But it wouldn't be a stretch to imagine -

71
00:05:19.267 --> 00:05:23.217
- that you think of women as disposable pleasures.
rather feminine pursuits.

72
00:05:24.997 --> 00:05:29.547
So as charming as you are. Mr. Bond. I will be keeping
an eye of our government's money -

73
00:05:29.747 --> 00:05:31.917
- and off of your perfectly formed ass.

74
00:05:32.117 --> 00:05:35.867
- You noticed? - Even accountants have imagination.

75
00:05:35.877 --> 00:05:40.717
- How was your lamb? - Stewed. my sympathys.

76
00:05:42.597 --> 00:05:46.607
- Good evening. mr. Bond. - Good evening. miss Lynd.

77
00:06:01.387 --> 00:06:05.307
- Hotel Splendide. sir? - That's right.

78
00:06:06.037 --> 00:06:08.017
- Thank you. sir. - Thank you.

79
00:06:21.517 --> 00:06:23.867
It's last minutes details.

80
00:06:25.187 --> 00:06:27.337
Apparently. we're very much in love.

81
00:06:28.247 --> 00:06:32.657
- Do you usually leave it to the porter to tell you this
sort of things? - Only when it's a necessary brief.

82
00:06:33.227 --> 00:06:36.847
I am mr. Arlington Beach. a professional gambler.

83
00:06:36.847 --> 00:06:39.177
And you are miss Stephanie Broadchest...

84
00:06:39.457 --> 00:06:43.417
- You have to trust me on this. - You know I don't.

85
00:06:43.417 --> 00:06:47.497
We've been involved quite awhile. hence the shared suite.

86
00:06:47.697 --> 00:06:52.867
But my familiy is strict roman catholic. therefore
for prudence's sake it will be a two bedroom suite.

87
00:06:53.067 --> 00:06:56.537
I do hate it. when religion comes between us.

88
00:06:56.743 --> 00:06:58.723
Religion and a securely locked door.

89
00:06:59.253 --> 00:07:04.043
- Am I going to have a problem with you. Bond? -
No. don't worry. you're not my type.

90
00:07:04.213 --> 00:07:07.343
- Smart? - Single.

91
00:07:26.023 --> 00:07:30.773
- Welcome to the Hotel Splendide. what is your name. sir. -
James Bond. You'll find the reservation under "Beach".

92
00:07:30.773 --> 00:07:35.763
- Welcome. mr. Bond. - You sign right there.
you represent the treasury.

93
00:07:40.443 --> 00:07:44.443
- Thank you. enjoy your stay. - I will.

94
00:07:47.923 --> 00:07:49.483
Very funny.

95
00:07:49.513 --> 00:07:53.363
Look. Le Chiffre knows I'm well connected. he also knows
who I am and where the money is coming from.

96
00:07:53.363 --> 00:07:55.353
Which means he has decided to play me anyway.

97
00:07:55.603 --> 00:07:59.663
He is either desperate or he is overly confident.  But either way. that tells me something about him.

98
00:07:59.933 --> 00:08:02.763
And all he gets in return is a name that he already has.

99
00:08:03.223 --> 00:08:07.703
You know he knows something about you.
He knows you are reckless.

100
00:08:07.703 --> 00:08:11.883
Take the next one. It isn't room enough for me and your ego.

101
00:08:12.833 --> 00:08:16.613
- Mr. Bond. this is for you. - Thank you.

102
00:08:46.283 --> 00:08:48.263
I love you too. M.

103
00:09:25.583 --> 00:09:29.543
My name is Mathis. Rene Mathis. I am your contact here.

104
00:09:33.673 --> 00:09:37.623
- Does he know we have been watching him? -
Le Chiffre? I don't think so.

105
00:09:38.333 --> 00:09:41.723
Probably because there is no "we". Just me.

106
00:09:43.113 --> 00:09:48.213
I'm afraid if you get into trouble here.
recovery won't come over the next hill.

107
00:09:50.333 --> 00:09:52.313
Le Chiffre arrived yesterday.

108
00:09:52.443 --> 00:09:55.573
I've spent the time reestablishing old relationships.

109
00:09:56.393 --> 00:09:58.663
The cief of police is here now. very close.

110
00:09:59.323 --> 00:10:03.283
It is him. with the mustache. over my left shoulder.

111
00:10:04.133 --> 00:10:08.083
- That can make life quite difficult. - And quite possible shorter.

112
00:10:08.363 --> 00:10:10.343
He is not a very subtile man.

113
00:10:10.993 --> 00:10:13.253
I thought about buying his services. but -

114
00:10:13.453 --> 00:10:17.313
- but quite franky. I couldn't afford to outbid Le Chiffre.

115
00:10:25.393 --> 00:10:30.343
I hate to say it. but the accountants seem to be
running MI6 these days.

116
00:10:31.543 --> 00:10:34.543
Not that I have anything against accauntants.

117
00:10:34.543 --> 00:10:36.693
Many of them are lovely.

118
00:10:37.683 --> 00:10:41.473
So I decided it was cheeper to supply his deputy with evidence -

119
00:10:41.503 --> 00:10:44.943
- that we were bribing the chief.

120
00:10:44.943 --> 00:10:48.893
It's amazing what we can do with Photoshop these days. isn't it.

121
00:10:51.953 --> 00:10:54.433
I think your odds are improving. mr Bond.

122
00:10:59.733 --> 00:11:03.683
- Yes? - For you.

123
00:11:04.333 --> 00:11:06.303
Something you expect med to wear?

124
00:11:09.143 --> 00:11:10.693
I need you to look fabulous. -

125
00:11:10.893 --> 00:11:17.443
- so when you walk up behind me and kiss me on my neck. the players will think about your neckline and not their cards.

126
00:11:17.473 --> 00:11:19.453
Do you think you can do that for me?

127
00:11:19.833 --> 00:11:21.813
I'll do my best.

128
00:11:22.423 --> 00:11:24.403
Thank you.

129
00:11:36.023 --> 00:11:40.473
- I have a dinner jacket. - There are dinner jackets
and there are dinner jackets.

130
00:11:40.983 --> 00:11:44.953
This is the latter. and I need you looking like
a man who belongs at that table.

131
00:11:45.253 --> 00:11:47.233
How...

132
00:11:47.713 --> 00:11:51.763
- It is tailored. - I sliced you up when we met.

133
00:12:43.463 --> 00:12:47.413
- Good evening. sir. - Good evening.

134
00:12:47.663 --> 00:12:49.643
Thank you.

135
00:12:59.933 --> 00:13:03.893
Then you must be mr. Bliss' replacement. Welcome. mr. Beach.

136
00:13:05.243 --> 00:13:08.113
Or is that Bond? I am a little confused.

137
00:13:08.123 --> 00:13:10.103
Oh. we wouldn't want that. would we?

138
00:13:13.783 --> 00:13:16.263
Monsieur Mendel. Please sit down.

139
00:13:19.723 --> 00:13:21.923
Ladies and gentlemen. welcome.

140
00:13:21.963 --> 00:13:26.773
As you know. the game is "no limit". Hold'em poker.
Five communual cards and two on the hold.

141
00:13:26.773 --> 00:13:30.243
Monsieur Mendel represents the Basel banks in
Switzerland holding the sticks.

142
00:13:31.683 --> 00:13:35.383
Mesdames et messieurs. You have each
deposited $10 millions buy in.

143
00:13:35.383 --> 00:13:38.443
Further buy in of $5 million can be made by electronic transfer.

144
00:13:38.443 --> 00:13:44.433
The money will remain in ascrow until the winner
enters his password into the encrypter.

145
00:13:44.673 --> 00:13:49.123
Whereupon the entire sum will be wired to
any bank account in the world you nominate.

146
00:13:49.313 --> 00:13:51.283
Mr. Bond?

147
00:13:51.293 --> 00:13:55.253
We proceed alphabetically. Please be so kind
as to enter a password of your choice.

148
00:14:02.963 --> 00:14:04.943
Six letters or more.

149
00:14:16.643 --> 00:14:18.613
High card from dealer position.

150
00:14:26.103 --> 00:14:30.543
Monsieur Gallardo. mr. Kaminoksky has a small blind for $5000. -

151
00:14:30.573 --> 00:14:33.633
- and mr. Fukutu the big blind for $10.000.

152
00:14:36.583 --> 00:14:38.563
Enjoy the game.

153
00:15:00.713 --> 00:15:02.693
Four players.

154
00:15:03.873 --> 00:15:05.853
Your bet?

155
00:15:06.893 --> 00:15:09.263
Check. Check.

156
00:15:14.453 --> 00:15:16.383
Bet $50.000.

157
00:15:28.993 --> 00:15:30.973
Call.

158
00:15:33.863 --> 00:15:35.763
Fold.

159
00:15:36.803 --> 00:15:38.783
Fold. Heads-up.

160
00:15:43.033 --> 00:15:45.013
Monsieur Le Chiffre?

161
00:15:55.593 --> 00:15:57.573
Bet $100.000.

162
00:16:01.033 --> 00:16:06.173
- You were supposed to enter so the others
could see you. - Was I? Forgive me.

163
00:16:07.653 --> 00:16:09.633
Good luck darling.

164
00:16:13.393 --> 00:16:15.373
It's up to you. monsieur Bond.

165
00:16:17.343 --> 00:16:21.303
- Monsieur Bond? - Excuse me. what was the bet? $100.000?

166
00:16:22.093 --> 00:16:24.073
Call.

167
00:16:30.103 --> 00:16:33.653
I suppose I don't have to tell you how beautiful you look?

168
00:16:33.663 --> 00:16:36.633
Half the people at that table are still watching you.

169
00:16:36.833 --> 00:16:38.803
Champagne.

170
00:16:41.573 --> 00:16:43.553
Monsieur Le Chiffre?

171
00:16:53.643 --> 00:16:55.613
Bet $200.000.

172
00:17:01.253 --> 00:17:04.223
Monsieur. you have been called. Show your cards please.

173
00:17:06.293 --> 00:17:09.563
Full house to monsieur Le Chiffre. 9's over 2's.

174
00:17:09.753 --> 00:17:11.733
Mr. Bond?

175
00:17:14.013 --> 00:17:15.983
Fold.

176
00:17:22.313 --> 00:17:24.293
Send the barman over. please.

177
00:17:32.793 --> 00:17:34.773
Dry Martini. Wait.

178
00:17:35.663 --> 00:17:40.903
Three measures of Gordon's. one of vodka. half a measure of China Lillet. Shake up. add some ice and a thin slice of lemon.

179
00:17:41.403 --> 00:17:44.063
- Yes. sir. - Bruno. I'll have one of those.

180
00:17:44.073 --> 00:17:46.933
- So will I. - Certainly.

181
00:17:48.023 --> 00:17:50.793
Fred. bring me one as well. and keep the fruit.

182
00:17:52.473 --> 00:17:54.453
That's it?

183
00:17:55.273 --> 00:17:58.783
- Anyone wants play poker now? - One's in a hurry.

184
00:18:06.613 --> 00:18:08.593
Will you excuse me.

185
00:18:21.353 --> 00:18:24.503
- Taste nice - I thought we dispenced the covers.

186
00:18:24.513 --> 00:18:29.263
No. we dispenced with one that was of no use
and created another that is.

187
00:18:29.753 --> 00:18:31.733
- Is he watching? - Yes.

188
00:18:32.123 --> 00:18:37.073
This is mean character. pissed off because
you're loosing so fast we won't be here past midnight.

189
00:18:37.273 --> 00:18:41.223
I'll bring my character's feelings mirror my own.

190
00:18:42.823 --> 00:18:46.783
You know that's not half bad.
I must come up with a name for that.

191
00:18:48.183 --> 00:18:50.533
He was worth it. To discover his talent.

192
00:18:51.113 --> 00:18:54.693
- What do you mean? - The twich he has to hide when he bluffs.

193
00:18:54.693 --> 00:18:58.543
- Bluffs? He had the best hand. - Which he got on the last card.

194
00:18:58.543 --> 00:19:01.003
The odds against was 23 to 1 and he knew that.

195
00:19:01.203 --> 00:19:03.173
When he did his first raise he had nothing.

196
00:19:03.373 --> 00:19:05.743
Then it was blind luck. You got the bug?

197
00:19:05.943 --> 00:19:07.923
Yes.

198
00:19:08.513 --> 00:19:10.493
Thank you.

199
00:19:13.463 --> 00:19:15.633
Maybe he can fix his deposit half.

200
00:19:24.533 --> 00:19:28.693
Ladies and gentlemen. Mesdames et messieurs.
We have now been playing for 4 hours.

201
00:19:28.883 --> 00:19:32.843
It's time for a short break. We will resume play in one hour.

202
00:20:01.013 --> 00:20:05.343
Well. I think I will report about the evenings "florentines".

203
00:20:09.923 --> 00:20:11.903
- Sir. - You wanted to do what to me?

204
00:20:12.203 --> 00:20:16.153
- You've lost me completely. - You said you couldn't
wait to have me back in the room. Come on.

205
00:20:39.393 --> 00:20:41.373
So what's so damned important?

206
00:20:44.833 --> 00:20:46.803
I'm so..

207
00:20:49.473 --> 00:20:51.453
Where is my money?

208
00:20:55.013 --> 00:20:57.983
- Good evening. - You're holding a parcel for me?

209
00:21:02.733 --> 00:21:04.703
Thank you.

210
00:21:05.793 --> 00:21:09.753
You think you can loose that kind of money
and no one will notice?

211
00:21:10.643 --> 00:21:12.613
You money is safe.

212
00:21:13.703 --> 00:21:15.683
Open that.

213
00:21:30.913 --> 00:21:34.963
You'll have it tomorrow. All of it.

214
00:21:47.923 --> 00:21:52.073
I will take a hand for this treason.
but you need to use yours.

215
00:21:56.223 --> 00:21:58.203
Hold out your arm.

216
00:21:59.193 --> 00:22:01.173
Hold out your arm. my beaty.

217
00:22:01.463 --> 00:22:03.443
Or I'll take your head.

218
00:22:12.443 --> 00:22:14.523
Go to the room. Wait for me there.

219
00:22:27.823 --> 00:22:29.793
Stairs.

220
00:22:33.303 --> 00:22:35.283
Not a world of protest.

221
00:22:36.273 --> 00:22:38.453
Should find a new boyfriend.

222
00:24:35.923 --> 00:24:40.673
Go find Mathis. tell him I've hidden the bodies
down here. and I want him to get rid of them.

223
00:24:41.163 --> 00:24:43.143
Do that now. Go. Go!

224
00:25:44.453 --> 00:25:46.423
You've changed your shirt. mr. Bond.

225
00:25:46.923 --> 00:25:49.893
I hope our game doesn't make you transpire?

226
00:25:50.973 --> 00:25:56.113
A little. but I don't consider myself in trouble
until I start wheeping blood.

227
00:25:56.123 --> 00:25:59.283
Ladies and gentlemen. if everybody's ready.
let's continue the game.

228
00:26:58.713 --> 00:27:01.683
The blood on my hands are not coming off.

229
00:27:03.653 --> 00:27:05.633
May I see.

230
00:27:20.363 --> 00:27:22.343
That's better?

231
00:27:26.103 --> 00:27:28.473
- Cold? - Yes.

232
00:28:25.633 --> 00:28:29.583
- Any trouble with the bodies? - Not at all.

233
00:28:43.233 --> 00:28:46.693
Being dead doesn't mean one still can't be helpful.

234
00:28:47.583 --> 00:28:52.523
Le Chiffre will keep looking over his shoulder.
wondering who it will come from next.

235
00:28:54.113 --> 00:28:56.083
How is our girl?

236
00:28:56.683 --> 00:28:59.253
Melted your cold heart?

237
00:29:17.443 --> 00:29:20.013
- Fold. - Fold.

238
00:29:20.223 --> 00:29:22.383
And fold.

239
00:29:23.393 --> 00:29:25.183
Three players.

240
00:29:27.533 --> 00:29:30.713
- Monsieur? - 300 grand.

241
