- Vodka Martini. - Shaken or stirred?

283
00:34:11.343 --> 00:34:13.323
Do I look like I give a damn?

284
00:34:30.363 --> 00:34:32.343
- James. get the girl.

285
00:34:41.093 --> 00:34:44.363
Sorry. I should introduce myself since we seem related.

286
00:34:44.553 --> 00:34:47.323
Felix Leiter. A brother from Langley.

287
00:34:49.303 --> 00:34:53.263
You shall have a little faith. You keep your
head above you. I think you have him.

288
00:34:53.283 --> 00:34:55.233
Had. Excuse me.

289
00:34:56.023 --> 00:35:00.373
- You're not buying in? - No.

290
00:35:04.133 --> 00:35:07.883
Listen. I'm bleeding chips. I'm not gonna last much longer.

291
00:35:07.893 --> 00:35:10.073
You have a better chance. I'll stake you.

292
00:35:11.053 --> 00:35:13.823
I'm saying I'll give you the money to keep going.

293
00:35:14.023 --> 00:35:17.983
Just one thing. If it bought off. the CIA brings him in.

294
00:35:19.953 --> 00:35:21.933
And what about the winnings?

295
00:35:22.723 --> 00:35:24.903
Does it look like we need the money?

296
00:35:36.273 --> 00:35:38.253
Shall we up the blinds?

297
00:35:40.133 --> 00:35:42.103
Why not.

298
00:35:45.173 --> 00:35:47.153
Bet.

299
00:35:48.433 --> 00:35:50.413
Rise.

300
00:36:09.403 --> 00:36:11.373
Excuse me.

301
00:36:16.233 --> 00:36:20.033
- Call. - Rise $500.000.

302
00:36:23.253 --> 00:36:25.453
- Fold. - Thank you.

303
00:36:27.443 --> 00:36:29.423
Fold.

304
00:36:32.333 --> 00:36:34.313
Fold.

305
00:37:01.113 --> 00:37:05.533
- Give me. - Sorry sir. you are big blind.

306
00:38:11.273 --> 00:38:13.553
- Who is it? - 007.

307
00:38:15.053 --> 00:38:19.003
Bond's being poisened. He's going into a cardiac arrest.

308
00:38:19.953 --> 00:38:24.563
Stay calm. don't interrupt. you will be dead within two minutes uness you do exactly like I tell you.

309
00:38:25.133 --> 00:38:28.603
- I'm all ears. - Remove the defillibrator from the couch.

310
00:38:28.603 --> 00:38:32.063
- Do we know what it is yet? - We're still scanning.

311
00:38:35.453 --> 00:38:37.683
Attach the leads to your chest.

312
00:38:46.623 --> 00:38:50.583
Ventricular takykardi - digitalis. What did they give him?

313
00:38:54.213 --> 00:38:57.503
- As soon as it reads charged ... the button ...
- Don't push the red button!

314
00:38:57.703 --> 00:39:00.173
- You hear me. don't push it yet.
- His heart's gonna stop.

315
00:39:00.373 --> 00:39:03.433
There is time for only one charge.

316
00:39:03.633 --> 00:39:07.083
Take the blue combi pen. Bond. Mid neck. Into the vein.

317
00:39:12.833 --> 00:39:17.613
You will pass out in a few seconds.
push the red button now. Bond!

318
00:39:23.213 --> 00:39:27.173
- Bond. push the red button. - Do it now!

319
00:40:11.663 --> 00:40:15.623
- You ok? - Me?

320
00:40:16.613 --> 00:40:20.963
- Thank you. - You're welcome. Take a trip to the hospital.

321
00:40:21.163 --> 00:40:23.133
I'll do.

322
00:40:23.923 --> 00:40:27.883
- Soon as I've won this game
- You're not seriously going back there.

323
00:40:30.453 --> 00:40:32.433
I wouldn't dream of it.

324
00:40:33.913 --> 00:40:35.893
Bet $1 million.

325
00:40:39.153 --> 00:40:42.713
- All in. - Gentllemen. showdown please.

326
00:40:44.913 --> 00:40:46.923
To pair. Aces and sevens

327
00:40:50.433 --> 00:40:52.403
Queen plays. Wins.

328
00:41:01.233 --> 00:41:05.103
I'm sorry.  The last hand almost killed me.

329
00:41:06.463 --> 00:41:11.383
Gentlemen. with this chip exchange we enter
the final phase of the game. There's no more buyings.

330
00:41:12.083 --> 00:41:14.133
The big blind is now $1 million dollars.

331
00:41:21.573 --> 00:41:23.553
Four players.

332
00:41:25.233 --> 00:41:27.213
It's your bet.

333
00:41:30.573 --> 00:41:32.553
- Monsieur Bond? - Check.

334
00:41:33.143 --> 00:41:35.673
$24 million in the pot already.

335
00:41:38.783 --> 00:41:42.323
- Check. - Check. All check.

336
00:41:43.073 --> 00:41:45.253
Four players.

337
00:41:49.113 --> 00:41:51.093
- Check. - Check.

338
00:41:55.743 --> 00:41:57.723
All in. $6 million.

339
00:41:58.643 --> 00:42:01.143
Bet. $6 millioner. All in.

340
00:42:06.353 --> 00:42:08.333
$5 million. All in.

341
00:42:08.743 --> 00:42:10.723
Bid is $6 million.

342
00:42:18.153 --> 00:42:20.123
Rise.

343
00:42:21.273 --> 00:42:23.523
Rise $12 million.

344
00:42:23.773 --> 00:42:25.753
Heads-up.

345
00:42:55.003 --> 00:42:57.193
$40.5 millioner. All in.

346
00:43:00.113 --> 00:43:02.093
Rise. All in.

347
00:43:20.303 --> 00:43:22.793
Well. I think I will call your lepard.

348
00:43:30.493 --> 00:43:31.973
Call.

349
00:43:42.703 --> 00:43:45.543
$150 millioner in the pot.

350
00:43:46.743 --> 00:43:48.623
Gentlemen. showdown please.

351
00:43:52.953 --> 00:43:55.193
Flush. Ace. king. queen.

352
00:44:03.143 --> 00:44:05.433
Full house. Eights and aces.

353
00:44:23.403 --> 00:44:25.383
Higher full house..

354
00:44:25.583 --> 00:44:27.273
Aces and six'es.

355
00:44:32.813 --> 00:44:34.783
Monsieur Bond?

356
00:44:50.123 --> 00:44:52.003
5 and 7 of spades.

357
00:44:53.033 --> 00:44:55.703
Straight Flush. 4 till 8.

358
00:44:55.923 --> 00:44:57.893
A high hand.

359
00:45:02.583 --> 00:45:03.833
Monsieur Bond wins.

360
00:45:04.833 --> 00:45:08.293
- Please. - Thank you very much.

361
00:45:10.853 --> 00:45:14.803
- He is all yours. - I appreciate it. brother.

362
00:45:20.943 --> 00:45:22.213
Congratulations.

363
00:45:22.213 --> 00:45:26.163
- You know it is no celebration in it.
- You were almost dead an hour ago.

364
00:45:27.543 --> 00:45:29.523
Come on. I'm finished.

365
00:45:49.273 --> 00:45:53.383
Mathis says the americans have contacted Le Chiffre.

366
00:45:53.383 --> 00:45:55.453
They think to extract him before dawn.

367
00:45:56.613 --> 00:45:58.723
You know. I think I would call that a Vesper.

368
00:45:59.793 --> 00:46:02.893
- Is it the after taste? - No.

369
00:46:02.903 --> 00:46:06.863
Because once you have tasted it. that's all you want to cook.

370
00:46:08.373 --> 00:46:12.453
- That was quite a good line. - That's a very good line.

371
00:46:12.453 --> 00:46:15.563
- But you're laughing at it. - Not so much because of you.

372
00:46:15.763 --> 00:46:17.733
Well. that's fine.

373
00:46:24.163 --> 00:46:26.343
I'll figure out what that is.

374
00:46:28.203 --> 00:46:31.713
- It's an algerian love knot. - Really?

375
00:46:31.713 --> 00:46:34.743
- I thought it was just pretty. - No.

376
00:46:36.133 --> 00:46:38.103
Someone gave it to you.

377
00:46:41.243 --> 00:46:43.223
He is a very lucky man.

378
00:46:48.963 --> 00:46:51.493
You can switch off so easily. can't you?

379
00:46:51.923 --> 00:46:54.263
Doesn't bother you killing these people?

380
00:46:54.603 --> 00:46:58.343
I wouldn't be much if I did.

381
00:46:58.533 --> 00:47:00.513
I don't believe you.

382
00:47:01.283 --> 00:47:03.263
You got a choice you know.

383
00:47:03.653 --> 00:47:07.203
Just because you've done something.
doesn't mean you keep doing it.

384
00:47:07.393 --> 00:47:10.723
Why is it people who can't take advice also insist giving it?

385
00:47:10.723 --> 00:47:13.633
Are you thinking I don't take my own advice?

386
00:47:13.663 --> 00:47:15.643
I think something is driving you.

387
00:47:16.253 --> 00:47:20.213
And I think I'll never find out what it is.

388
00:47:24.023 --> 00:47:25.993
Mathis needs me.

389
00:47:26.753 --> 00:47:29.523
Good night. Congratulations again.

390
00:47:47.723 --> 00:47:48.903
Mathis.

391
00:49:37.183 --> 00:49:43.493
I'm afraid your friend Mathis. is really ... my friend.

392
00:51:20.373 --> 00:51:22.093
Bond ...

393
00:51:22.093 --> 00:51:24.263
You've taken good care about your body.

394
00:51:31.343 --> 00:51:33.323
Such a vaste.

395
00:51:50.143 --> 00:51:54.833
You know. I've never understood these levelled tortures.

396
00:51:55.433 --> 00:51:57.593
It's the simplest things -

397
00:51:57.603 --> 00:52:00.763
-to cause more pain than a man can possibly enjoy.

398
00:52:02.943 --> 00:52:09.073
And of course. it's not only the immediate pain.
but the knowledge that if you don't give up quickly enough-

399
00:52:10.453 --> 00:52:13.913
- there will be not much left to define you as a man.

400
00:52:19.653 --> 00:52:21.633
The only question remains...

401
00:52:22.893 --> 00:52:24.873
Will you give up in time?

402
00:52:26.873 --> 00:52:28.853
I want the money.

403
00:52:47.543 --> 00:52:51.663
Miss Lynd will give me the account number.
if she has not already.

404
00:52:51.663 --> 00:52:53.883
So all I need from you is the password.

405
00:53:03.093 --> 00:53:05.143
The password.. please.

406
00:53:10.283 --> 00:53:13.253
I've gotten an itch.. down there.

407
00:53:14.903 --> 00:53:16.873
Would you mind?

408
00:53:24.123 --> 00:53:26.593
No! No!

409
00:53:29.103 --> 00:53:31.483
To the right. to the right. to the right.

410
00:53:31.933 --> 00:53:33.913
You are a funny man. mr. Bond.

411
00:53:38.713 --> 00:53:41.073
Yes. yes. yes!

412
00:53:47.363 --> 00:53:51.513
Now the whole world's gonna know that
you died while scratching my balls.

413
00:53:53.893 --> 00:53:56.563
I died? I died ...?

414
00:53:56.753 --> 00:54:00.403
Yes. because no matter what you do.
I'm not gonna give you the password -

415
00:54:00.413 --> 00:54:05.063
- which means that your clients will hunt you down and cut you in little pieces of meat while you're still breathing.

416
00:54:05.433 --> 00:54:09.013
Because if you kill me. there will be nowhere else to hide.

417
00:54:09.023 --> 00:54:11.093
But you are so wrong!

418
00:54:11.943 --> 00:54:14.363
Because after I've slaughted you and your little girlfriend-

419
00:54:14.553 --> 00:54:17.423
- your people will still welcome me with open arms.

420
00:54:33.313 --> 00:54:35.293
Give me the password.

421
00:54:35.723 --> 00:54:37.703
And I will at least let her live.

422
00:54:41.723 --> 00:54:45.673
Do it soon enough. she will still be in one peace.

423
00:54:56.683 --> 00:55:00.143
- You really arn't going to tell me? - No.

424
00:55:02.593 --> 00:55:04.573
So I think ... -

425
00:55:08.543 --> 00:55:12.503
- I will feed you with what you have undone.

426
00:55:24.343 --> 00:55:26.313
I'll get the money.

427
00:55:27.303 --> 00:55:29.283
Tell them. I'll get the money.

428
00:55:29.903 --> 00:55:33.663
Money isn't as valuable to our organisation as the ability to trust.

429
00:56:38.333 --> 00:56:40.313
Any ideas?

430
00:56:42.683 --> 00:56:46.343
- What? - Why he left the two of you alive.

431
00:56:48.423 --> 00:56:50.403
Where is she?

432
00:56:50.793 --> 00:56:52.773
Sleeping.

433
00:56:53.333 --> 00:56:55.923
And I'm supposed to make you drink this.

434
00:56:57.213 --> 00:56:59.193
It's just odd.

435
00:56:59.473 --> 00:57:02.303
Killing all. but leaving you and her untouched.

436
00:57:03.283 --> 00:57:07.323
Almost like someone tried to tell us something.

437
00:57:07.323 --> 00:57:09.303
Did you look at the killer?

438
00:57:10.103 --> 00:57:12.083
No.

439
00:57:12.853 --> 00:57:14.833
Shame.

440
00:57:16.133 --> 00:57:18.103
Drink up.

441
00:57:21.053 --> 00:57:23.233
Anything else you remember?

442
00:57:23.523 --> 00:57:27.173
- Anything else that can help us? - Help us?

443
00:57:27.183 --> 00:57:29.163
Or help you?

444
00:58:08.263 --> 00:58:10.383
- Hello. - Hello.

445
00:58:12.773 --> 00:58:14.603
You're all right?

446
00:58:14.633 --> 00:58:17.363
I came just to waking you.

447
00:58:17.393 --> 00:58:21.353
You're always looking at me
like you haven't seen me in years.

448
00:58:22.363 --> 00:58:24.343
Makes me feel reborn.

449
00:58:28.293 --> 00:58:30.273
If you've just been born -

450
00:58:31.583 --> 00:58:33.563
- would you be naked?

451
00:58:34.593 --> 00:58:36.573
You have me there.

452
00:58:39.173 --> 00:58:41.153
You can have me anyway.

453
00:58:43.473 --> 00:58:44.653
I can?

454
00:58:45.673 --> 00:58:48.163
Yes. here. there. any way you like.

455
00:58:50.173 --> 00:58:55.183
- Does this mean that you will make love to me?
- Yes. that's how I would describe it.

456
00:58:55.383 --> 00:59:00.073
Not long ago. if you described your feeling about me not long ago..

457
00:59:01.523 --> 00:59:05.183
..I'm trying to find a better word than "nobody".

458
00:59:05.193 --> 00:59:07.173
I'm afraid I'm a complicated woman.

459
00:59:08.493 --> 00:59:10.483
That's something to be afraid of.

460
00:59:12.993 --> 00:59:14.963
Hello.

461
00:59:15.363 --> 00:59:17.343
Perfect timing.

462
00:59:18.473 --> 00:59:21.383
Mr. Mendel. how are things in Switzerland?

463
00:59:21.393 --> 00:59:25.453
My apologies. I do not mean to rush.
but $120 million is a large sum of money.

464
00:59:25.643 --> 00:59:28.213
It certainly is. You didn't bring anyt chocolate with you?

465
00:59:28.413 --> 00:59:30.393
I'm afraid not.

466
00:59:31.593 --> 00:59:34.153
If you would type in the account number.

467
00:59:41.203 --> 00:59:45.243
- And then the password - You can do that.

468
00:59:45.273 --> 00:59:47.253
I would if I knew what it was.

469
00:59:47.403 --> 00:59:53.333
V ... E ... S ... P ... E ... R.

470
01:00:04.113 --> 01:00:08.073
The account has been transferred. Sorry to disturbing you.

471
01:00:10.643 --> 01:00:12.423
- Auf wiedersehen. - Auf wiedersehen.

472
01:00:18.843 --> 01:00:20.823
You know. James?

473
01:00:21.993 --> 01:00:25.853
I just want you to know that if all that was left of you... -

474
01:00:25.863 --> 01:00:28.923
- was your smile and your little finger ...

475
01:00:28.933 --> 01:00:32.893
you would be more of a man than anyone else.

476
01:00:40.423 --> 01:00:44.383
That's because you know what I can do with my little finger.

477
01:00:46.733 --> 01:00:50.683
- I have no idea. - But you're aching to find out..

478
01:00:53.823 --> 01:00:56.213
You're not going to let me in there?

479
01:00:57.983 --> 01:00:59.963
You got your armor back on.

480
01:01:02.943 --> 01:01:04.913
I have no armor left.

481
01:01:06.533 --> 01:01:08.503
You stripped it from me.

482
01:01:09.843 --> 01:01:11.823
What there is left of me.

483
01:01:12.723 --> 01:01:14.693
Whatever is left of me..

484
01:01:16.063 --> 01:01:18.043
Whatever I am..

485
01:01:18.423 --> 01:01:20.403
I'm yours.

486
01:02:19.683 --> 01:02:21.953
M won't miss me for a couple of days.

487
01:02:23.283 --> 01:02:26.123
- She'll be too busy sweating Mathis. - Mathis?

488
01:02:26.123 --> 01:02:30.653
Remember. what I told you about Le Chiffre.
Mathis told Le Chiffre.

489
01:02:31.593 --> 01:02:32.823
That's how he won me out.

490
01:02:33.023 --> 01:02:36.983
The same goes for the implant. I'm not going to miss that.

491
01:02:37.013 --> 01:02:40.453
- I can't believe that. - Neither could I.

492
01:02:41.273 --> 01:02:43.243
I thougth he hid my back.

493
01:02:44.213 --> 01:02:46.193
But there you go.

494
01:02:47.193 --> 01:02:49.343
Does everyone have a toll?

495
01:02:51.183 --> 01:02:53.153
Yes.

496
01:02:55.683 --> 01:02:57.663
Yes. everyone.

497
01:02:57.853 --> 01:02:59.833
Everyone except you.

498
01:03:03.973 --> 01:03:06.163
That's why I love you.

499
01:03:07.953 --> 01:03:09.923
Do you love me?

500
01:03:10.113 --> 01:03:15.253
Enough to float around the world with you.
until one of us must find an honest job.

501
01:03:15.653 --> 01:03:19.603
But I think that's gonna be you.
because I have no idea what an honest job is.

502
01:03:20.213 --> 01:03:22.193
Are you serious?

503
01:03:22.383 --> 01:03:23.603
Like you said ...

504
01:03:24.863 --> 01:03:28.813
If you do what I do for too long.
then there'll not be any soul left to salvage.

505
01:03:29.513 --> 01:03:33.473
I'm leaving with all that I have left.

506
01:03:34.243 --> 01:03:35.723
Is that enough for you?

507
01:05:17.983 --> 01:05:21.163
No stop. I've gotta go to the bank.

508
01:05:21.833 --> 01:05:23.013
What's the time?

509
01:05:25.583 --> 01:05:28.353
How much do you think we need to float for a month?

510
01:05:28.553 --> 01:05:30.743
I got plenty.

511
01:05:30.773 --> 01:05:33.593
I want to pay for my half.

512
01:05:37.053 --> 01:05:39.033
You stopped wearing your necklace.

513
01:05:39.433 --> 01:05:41.463
Yes. It was time.

514
01:05:42.623 --> 01:05:44.603
Time enough to look after the soul?

515
01:05:49.753 --> 01:05:52.273
You realize that one cannot always forget the past.

516
01:06:01.183 --> 01:06:03.363
Apparently not for your employer.

517
01:06:07.613 --> 01:06:09.593
Back in one month.

518
01:06:11.763 --> 01:06:15.723
Come on. I get money. you get supplies.

519
01:06:44.603 --> 01:06:46.583
Be back here in half an hour.

520
01:07:09.963 --> 01:07:13.363
- Hello. M. - I got your note.

521
01:07:13.393 --> 01:07:16.923
- Yes? - We'll talk about that later.

522
01:07:16.933 --> 01:07:19.453
Right now I have a man from treasury here.

523
01:07:19.653 --> 01:07:23.603
He wonders if you ever is going to deposit the winnings.

524
01:07:25.243 --> 01:07:28.473
That's a shame. I didn't think they'd miss it.

525
01:07:28.693 --> 01:07:31.823
Yes. I told them not to worry.

526
01:07:32.113 --> 01:07:36.063
- So you'll deposit today?
- I'm on my way to the bank right now.

527
01:07:37.423 --> 01:07:39.393
James Bond for mr. Mendel.

528
01:07:41.603 --> 01:07:45.223
Mr Mendel. I have some trouble accessing
the funds of my account.

529
01:07:45.223 --> 01:07:49.173
It was transferred to the bank account number
your company gave us. Mr. Bond.

530
01:07:51.993 --> 01:07:54.463
It appears the money is being drawn as we speak.

531
01:07:57.273 --> 01:07:58.463
Where?

532
01:07:58.663 --> 01:08:01.813
The Venece branch of course. at St. Mark's Square.

533
01:08:01.823 --> 01:08:05.783
Is there a problem. mr. Bond?

534
01:10:12.253 --> 01:10:16.203
- I'll kill her! - Allow me.

535
01:14:24.473 --> 01:14:26.453
I'm sorry. James.

536
01:17:30.213 --> 01:17:32.383
She had a boy friend. a French Algerian.

537
01:17:33.113 --> 01:17:35.083
They were vey much in love.

538
01:17:35.453 --> 01:17:38.403
He was kidnapped by the organisation behind Le Chiffre.

539
01:17:38.403 --> 01:17:43.073
And they blackmailed her and wanted to kill him.
unless she cooperated.

540
01:17:43.583 --> 01:17:49.193
We should have picked up on it. but sometimes we're so
focused on our enemies. we forget to watch our friends.

541
01:17:50.483 --> 01:17:52.463
How are you doing?

542
01:17:52.563 --> 01:17:54.923
She left her cell phone.

543
01:17:54.933 --> 01:17:56.913
She must have known I'd check it.

544
01:17:57.963 --> 01:17:59.933
She knew you were you.

545
01:18:00.763 --> 01:18:03.613
- Well. at least this clears Mathis. - No.

546
01:18:03.643 --> 01:18:07.593
- No? - No. it just proves that he's guilty. not innocent.

547
01:18:07.783 --> 01:18:09.963
Could be a double blind.

548
01:18:10.853 --> 01:18:14.603
- You don't trust anyone. do you. James? - No.

549
01:18:14.613 --> 01:18:16.583
Then you've learned your lesson.

550
01:18:17.223 --> 01:18:20.493
Come back as soon as you can. we need you.

551
01:18:20.493 --> 01:18:22.473
Will do.

552
01:18:22.963 --> 01:18:26.773
- If you do need time ...
- Why should I need more time?

553
01:18:27.603 --> 01:18:29.433
Job's done.

554
01:18:29.443 --> 01:18:31.893
The bitch is dead.

555
01:18:31.933 --> 01:18:33.853
James?

556
01:18:33.893 --> 01:18:37.843
Did you ever asked yourself.
why you weren't killed that night?

557
01:18:37.873 --> 01:18:43.053
Isn't that obvious? She made a deal
to spare your life in exchange for the money.

558
01:18:43.303 --> 01:18:47.133
She hoped they would let her live.

559
01:18:47.143 --> 01:18:50.343
But she must have known. she had to have her death.

560
01:18:50.373 --> 01:18:54.533
And now we'll never know who was behind this.

561
01:18:54.573 --> 01:18:56.543
The trail's gone cold.

562
01:20:20.053 --> 01:20:23.773
- Hello? - Mr. White? We need to talk.

563
01:20:24.033 --> 01:20:26.003
Who is this?

564
01:20:55.507 --> 01:20:58.004
The name's Bond. James Bond
